Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
  Author AI
  Description "Base image for SSH-key onboarding task. Installs Python, pytest and ssh-keygen; prepares writable /home/user."

%post
  set -e

  # Update package index and install required packages
  apt-get update
  DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        openssh-client \
        ca-certificates

  # Install pytest for the grader
  pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

  # Create an empty, writable home directory for the future user actions
  mkdir -p /home/user
  chmod 0777 /home/user

  # Clean up APT caches to keep the image lean
  apt-get clean
  rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%runscript
    chmod 755 /home/user

  exec "$@"

%help
  This container supplies:
  - ssh-keygen (from openssh-client) so students can create keys
  - pytest for the automated grading suite

  The workspace /home/user is writable and initially empty of any artefacts
  required by the assignment.